From aff865b680aeb6590e7ccc1a45b4890967106bda Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sanket Bumb <sanket@yourowncrm.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 18:27:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: unified save-then-open for popups, location color bands
 now persist
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Appointment dialog — unified pattern for ALL sub-screens (Collect Payment,
All Visits, Visit Notes, Audit Logs):
- saveThenOpen(targetName, openFn): validates form, saves appointment
  (create or update) using the SAME payload logic as the Save button
  (extracted into buildPayload()), shows 'Appointment saved.
  Opening <X>...' snackbar, closes the appointment dialog, then after
  200ms opens the target dialog centered with the freshly-saved
  appointment data
- Fixes data loss: previously Visit Notes/Logs closed the appointment
  dialog WITHOUT saving any in-progress edits
- Fixes positioning: previously Collect Payment/All Visits opened on
  top of the appointment dialog and rendered at the bottom of the page;
  now all four use the same close-then-reopen-centered flow
- save() refactored to use buildPayload() — removes duplicated payload
  construction logic

Location color bands — root cause fixed:
- ResourceScheduleController POST endpoint had a stub that NEVER
  persisted location_id when saving resource hours from the admin UI
  (comment said 'For now stored as null if not found')
  -> location_id was always null in the database regardless of what
     the user selected in Resource Hours
- Now actually looks up the Location by id and sets it on the schedule
- GET endpoint rewritten to return a plain DTO (ResourceScheduleResponse)
  with locationId/locationName/locationColor flattened out, avoiding
  lazy-loading serialization issues with the Location entity
- Frontend loadWorkingHours() simplified — uses locationColor directly
  from the DTO instead of a client-side location lookup map
- Resource Hours admin component: fixed reading 'location.id' (nested,
  no longer exists) -> 'locationId' (flat, matches new DTO) so the
  previously-saved location shows as selected when reopening the screen
